The primary analysis has been done usin Nextflow-Core RNASeq https://nf-co.re/rnaseq

setwd("/storage2/Bermejo/")

meta <- read_tsv("import.txt")
cond <- meta %>% dplyr::select(sample,condition) %>% column_to_rownames("sample")

table2 <- read_tsv("/storage2/Bermejo/nextflow/star_salmon/salmon.merged.transcript_counts.tsv")

We use DESeq2 package for secondary analysis and Quality Control

We remove those transcripts with a total abundance lower than 10

table_sum <- table2 %>% dplyr::select(-gene_id) %>% column_to_rownames("tx") %>% round()

dds_gene <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = table_sum %>% as.matrix(), 
                                   colData = cond, 
                                   design = ~condition)
## converting counts to integer mode
## Warning in DESeqDataSet(se, design = design, ignoreRank): some variables in
## design formula are characters, converting to factors
keep <- rowSums(counts(dds_gene)) >= 10
dds_gene <- dds_gene[keep,]
dds_gene <- DESeq(dds_gene)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates

Quality Control

To check the quality of the sample we test the homogenicity of the groups. In this case we represent the samples using Multi-Dimensional Scaling

mds <- counts(dds_gene, normalized = T) %>% 
  t() %>% vegdist(method = "binomial") %>% 
  metaMDS()

mds$points %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "sample") %>% inner_join(meta) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = MDS1, y = MDS2, label = sample, color = condition))  + geom_point() + geom_text_repel() + scale_color_d3()
## Joining, by = "sample"

To test the homogenicity we perform a PERMANOVA test

dist <- counts(dds_gene, normalized = T) %>% 
  t() %>% vegdist(method = "binomial")

adonis2(dist ~ condition, data = meta, permutations = 10000)
## Permutation test for adonis under reduced model
## Terms added sequentially (first to last)
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 10000
## 
## adonis2(formula = dist ~ condition, data = meta, permutations = 10000)
##           Df   SumOfSqs      R2      F Pr(>F)    
## condition  5 1593033939 0.17885 1.2197  3e-04 ***
## Residual  28 7313912423 0.82115                  
## Total     33 8906946362 1.00000                  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

The homogenicity of the groups is statistically significant so the sample quality is good enough

Importing annotation

We import biological annotation from ENSEMBL

mart <- useMart(biomart = "ENSEMBL_MART_ENSEMBL",
                dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl",
                host = 'https://www.ensembl.org')

ttg <- biomaRt::getBM(
  attributes = c("ensembl_transcript_id", "transcript_version",
                 "ensembl_gene_id", "external_gene_name", "description",
                 "transcript_biotype","entrezgene_id"),
  mart = mart)

Statistical Test

All the test were performed at transcript level to include lncRNA. you can find all the table results at https://github.com/irycisBioinfo/RnaSeqRosella

For each comparison we have performed an Gene Set Enrichment Analysis of GO term and KEGG pathways.

Control vs SIM

ctr_vs_sim_g <- results(dds_gene, contrast = c("condition","CTR","SIM"))

ctr_vs_sim_g %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "ensembl_transcript_id") %>%
  inner_join(ttg) %>% 
  write_tsv("ctr_vs_sim.tsv")
## Joining, by = "ensembl_transcript_id"
ctr_vs_sim_g %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "geneName") %>%
  mutate(sig = ifelse(padj < 0.01,"Significative","No-Significative")) %>%
  mutate(label = ifelse(sig == "Significative",geneName,NA)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x= log2FoldChange, y = -log10(padj), color = sig, size = sqrt(baseMean), label = label)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_text_repel(size = 1)+
  scale_color_d3() +
  theme_light() + labs(title = "Control vs SIM")
## Warning: Removed 37344 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
## Warning: Removed 132705 rows containing missing values (geom_text_repel).
## Warning: ggrepel: 440 unlabeled data points (too many overlaps). Consider
## increasing max.overlaps

ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich <- ctr_vs_sim_g %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = "ensembl_transcript_id") %>%
  filter(padj < 0.01) %>% inner_join(ttg) %>% 
  dplyr::select(entrezgene_id) %>% distinct() %>% drop_na() %>%  pull(entrezgene_id)
## Joining, by = "ensembl_transcript_id"
ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_go <- enrichGO(gene =ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich,
                                   OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
                                    ont           = "ALL",
                                    pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                                    pvalueCutoff  = 0.01,
                                    qvalueCutoff  = 0.05,
                                    readable      = TRUE)

if ((ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_go %>% as.data.frame() %>% nrow()) > 0  )
{
  barplot(ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_go, showCategory = 20)
} else{
  print("No enriched Pathways")
}

ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_kegg <- enrichKEGG(gene = ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich,
                                        organism     = 'hsa',
                                        pvalueCutoff = 0.05)
## Reading KEGG annotation online:
## 
## Reading KEGG annotation online:
if ((ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_kegg %>% as.data.frame() %>% nrow()) > 0  )
{
  barplot(ctr_vs_sim_g_enrich_kegg, showCategory = 20)
} else{
  print("No enriched Pathways")
}
## [1] "No enriched Pathways"
